I knew his father.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.199
Danish passport.

06:07.574 --> 06:11.704
His mother's side,
but he's only 24 years old.

06:14.790 --> 06:15.666
He'll do.

06:23.675 --> 06:27.135
I thought I would start with
some entry-level assignment,

06:27.137 --> 06:29.055
instead I got
a dream job.

06:30.514 --> 06:33.517
Special assistant to the
under secretary general.

06:34.644 --> 06:36.685
Running the largest
humanitarian program

06:36.687 --> 06:38.646
in the
United Nations history.

06:44.112 --> 06:45.530
I couldn't
believe my luck.

06:46.613 --> 06:49.950
All I kept thinking
was, "Don't fuck this up."

06:50.617 --> 06:53.243
The program is
called, "Oil For Food."

06:53.245 --> 06:55.079
It's created in 1995.

06:55.081 --> 06:58.291
By Security Council
resolution 986,

06:58.293 --> 07:01.084
which has stated that the
UN would manage the sale

07:01.086 --> 07:05.339
of Iraqi oil and use the profits
to provide humanitarian relief

07:05.341 --> 07:07.925
in the country to
alleviate the hardship.

07:07.927 --> 07:09.926
Which basically
means that our office

07:09.928 --> 07:12.512
is in charge of
trying to feed an entire nation,

07:12.514 --> 07:14.558
over 20 million people.

07:19.105 --> 07:21.441
You have a little
reading to catch up on.

07:21.733 --> 07:24.692
We are woefully behind schedule
on our funding status report

07:24.694 --> 07:25.860
to the
Security Council;

07:25.862 --> 07:28.570
Your immediate task will be to
help facilitate its completion.

07:28.572 --> 07:30.281
Your predecessor
was due to brief

07:30.283 --> 07:31.656
the undersecretary
tomorrow.

07:31.658 --> 07:33.159
Tomorrow?

07:33.161 --> 07:34.284
What happened to him?

07:34.286 --> 07:36.121
A car accident in Iraq.

07:49.093 --> 07:51.094
Jesus Christ!

07:51.096 --> 07:52.094
Is he alright?

07:52.096 --> 07:53.680
No,
he didn't make it.

07:53.682 --> 07:55.889
A bullet-point
summary will do.

07:55.891 --> 07:57.974
Pasha will be in
his office at nine.

08:34.221 --> 08:36.722
Got a couple
of minutes, Michael?

08:36.725 --> 08:39.142
Justin Cutter,
Central Intelligence.

08:39.144 --> 08:40.475
Really?

08:40.477 --> 08:43.438
Yeah, we come in
all shapes and sizes.

08:43.440 --> 08:45.772
Okay, can I help
you with something?

08:45.774 --> 08:49.776
Listen, we think Oil for Food is
being gamed for private gain

08:49.778 --> 08:52.405
by a bad guy or
bad guys unknown.

08:52.407 --> 08:54.364
Possibly with help
from the inside,

08:54.366 --> 08:56.408
which is where
you are, so...

08:56.410 --> 08:58.076
Look I-I just
got this job.

08:58.078 --> 09:00.371
I'm not gonna-
I'm not gonna spy for you.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.580
Oh God, no.

09:01.582 --> 09:03.583
No, no, leave that to
the professionals.

09:03.585 --> 09:05.292
I don't want
you to do anything

09:05.294 --> 09:08.212
that makes you
uncomfortable, Michael.

09:08.214 --> 09:10.757
Just keep your eyes and
ears open, that's all.

09:10.759 --> 09:12.009
For God and Country.

09:19.475 --> 09:22.517
I was aware going in
that the Oil for Food program

09:22.519 --> 09:25.648
had become something
of a political football.

09:27.775 --> 09:30.984
The program budget was
10 billon dollars a year.

09:30.986 --> 09:34.781
The entire rest of the UN
operational budget was only two.

09:34.783 --> 09:36.784
There was crazy
money to be had.

09:38.119 --> 09:41.536
Special interest
circling like buzzards.

09:41.538 --> 09:43.289
The program was simple.

09:43.291 --> 09:45.041
Because of the
economic sanctions imposed

09:45.043 --> 09:46.584
against Saddam Hussein

09:46.586 --> 09:50.504
after the first Gulf War,
Iraq's economy had crashed.

09:50.506 --> 09:52.422
People were
starving and dying

09:52.424 --> 09:56.009
from lack of basic
medicine and staples.

09:56.011 --> 09:58.304
The Oil for Food program
was designed to provide

09:58.306 --> 10:02.016
Iraqi citizens with what
they needed to survive.

10:02.018 --> 10:04.060
While at the same time,
preventing Saddam

10:04.062 --> 10:06.938
from developing his alleged
weapons of mass destruction.

10:08.774 --> 10:10.483
Under UN supervision,

10:10.485 --> 10:13.276
Iraqi oil was being sold
at market prices

10:13.278 --> 10:15.365
to pay
for humanitarian aid.

10:16.448 --> 10:20.033
Our job was to keep it funded
by making sure everything

10:20.035 --> 10:21.453
went by the book.

10:22.663 --> 10:24.122
I'm here to
present the summary.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.873
He'll be with
you in a minute.

10:25.875 --> 10:27.916
...This fucking
regime!

10:27.918 --> 10:29.042
Unbelievable.

10:29.044 --> 10:32.546
Yes, I sorted it as
always, a solution.

10:32.548 --> 10:35.590
Now we-we charted
a load of taxis, filled them,

10:35.592 --> 10:37.509
that should last
the outlying villages

10:37.511 --> 10:39.054
till we get
the trucks back.

10:41.682 --> 10:43.475
You call
this a summary?

10:46.395 --> 10:48.603
Fucking war and peace.

10:48.605 --> 10:50.605
Sorry sir, I was
trying to be thorough.

10:50.607 --> 10:52.150
Thorough?

10:52.152 --> 10:53.943
Yes, sir.

10:53.945 --> 10:56.487
Fuck.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.281
Well, just give me
the highlights kid,

10:58.283 --> 11:00.199
otherwise we'll be
here till spring thaw.

11:00.201 --> 11:03.536
Yes we have uhh, decreased
the malnutrition rate,

11:03.538 --> 11:06.830
reduced child mortality,
we've also uhh,

11:06.832 --> 11:11.502
made big strides in access
to water and electricity.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.588
There are
however some umm,

11:13.590 --> 11:16.340
systemic distribution failures
particularly in the North.

11:16.342 --> 11:21.304
The Kurds are getting shorted
uhh, wheat, milk, diesel fuel

11:21.306 --> 11:24.515
to the benefit of Tikrit,
who are getting seemingly

11:24.517 --> 11:25.724
more than
their fair share.

11:25.726 --> 11:28.935
Saddam's hometown,
what a surprise?

11:28.937 --> 11:30.188
Yeah.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.982
There are also all these
after service fees uhh,

11:32.984 --> 11:35.193
in the contracts.

11:35.195 --> 11:37.027
I'm pretty sure
they're kick-backs.

11:37.029 --> 11:40.156
If you wanna take a look, I uhh,
highlighted and aggregated them

11:40.158 --> 11:42.951
on page 26 to 29.

11:51.251 --> 11:53.002
It's a lot
of money, sir.

11:53.004 --> 11:56.548
In some places it's
as much as 30 percent.

12:02.971 --> 12:04.638
Sit.

12:05.600 --> 12:07.557
Kid.

12:07.559 --> 12:08.727
Sit down.

12:12.023 --> 12:13.772
The first rule of
diplomacy is that

12:13.774 --> 12:15.775
the truth is not
a matter of fact,

12:15.777 --> 12:18.026
it's a matter of consensus,
now consensus right now

12:18.028 --> 12:19.778
is that
sanctions are here to stay.

12:19.780 --> 12:22.031
The Americans and The
British will never lift them,

12:22.033 --> 12:26.661
which means that if you want
the people of Iraq to survive,

12:26.663 --> 12:28.787
we have to keep
Oil for Food running.

12:28.789 --> 12:30.580
Even with all
it's warts and flaws.

12:30.582 --> 12:31.999
Sir, you do
not need to...

12:32.001 --> 12:34.877
The second rule is to keep
your mouth shut and listen.

12:34.879 --> 12:36.628
Then if it suits,
you can talk.

12:36.630 --> 12:37.839
With discretion.

12:37.841 --> 12:41.469
Otherwise, keep your
cards, close to your vest.

12:43.263 --> 12:44.096
Yeah.

12:51.855 --> 12:55.605
Your father
was a good man.

12:58.235 --> 13:01.695
You should be so lucky
as to have his heart.

13:01.697 --> 13:03.323
Yeah, so
I've been told.

13:04.033 --> 13:07.826
We crossed paths
a couple of times.

13:07.828 --> 13:11.750
Must have
been 79', 80'.

13:12.625 --> 13:13.835
What a tragedy.

13:15.461 --> 13:16.629
Beirut.

13:18.548 --> 13:21.759
Fuck, I'm sorry.

13:23.761 --> 13:27.472
That must have been hard, a
boy growing up without a father.

13:27.474 --> 13:29.056
It was my normal.

13:29.058 --> 13:30.559
I had my cry.

13:34.063 --> 13:40.693
Good.

13:40.695 --> 13:42.570
Fix your summary.

13:42.572 --> 13:44.530
Go home and pack.

13:44.532 --> 13:46.991
We leave for
Baghdad on the red-eye.

13:46.993 --> 13:47.949
Uhh...

13:47.951 --> 13:50.953
What?
You have other plans?

13:50.955 --> 13:53.873
No, I don't.

13:53.875 --> 13:54.916
Of course not.

13:54.918 --> 13:56.041
Thank you.

14:31.830 --> 14:34.705
I was swept up
in the romance of it,

14:34.707 --> 14:36.833
I mean,
this is what I wanted.

14:36.835 --> 14:39.504
High adventure
and a worthy cause.

14:40.714 --> 14:43.341
It's like
Baghdad was my Casablanca.

14:45.927 --> 14:49.177
More or less sketchy,
crazy dangerous and stranger

14:49.179 --> 14:50.848
than I could've
ever imagined.

14:52.017 --> 14:55.727
The country lived in a state
of permanent self-occupation.

14:55.729 --> 14:59.188
