16:34.410 --> 16:35.701
Christina.

16:39.416 --> 16:40.248
Hassan Ghazarian.

16:40.250 --> 16:41.206
Hey, Michael Sullivan.

16:41.208 --> 16:42.208
Nice to meet you.

16:42.210 --> 16:43.209
Nice to meet you.

16:47.131 --> 16:48.839
Did you get the
documents I sent you?

16:48.841 --> 16:51.092
I did, I've even
printed them up for you.

16:51.094 --> 16:52.343
Oh great.

16:52.345 --> 16:53.930
You write well.

16:56.765 --> 17:00.892
60 percent of the Iraqi
people are solely dependent

17:00.894 --> 17:04.146
upon our
suppliers for survival.

17:04.147 --> 17:08.233
Wheat, grain, milk, medicine,
essential infrastructure.

17:08.236 --> 17:11.988
During our last ten months, we
have decreased malnutrition rate

17:11.990 --> 17:15.240
amongst children
in Iraq by 50 percent,

17:15.242 --> 17:20.287
thereby reduced
child mortality significantly.

17:20.289 --> 17:22.789
Okay, thank you very much,
photographers come through.

17:22.790 --> 17:25.375
We're gonna have a photo
opportunity with Madame Dupre.

17:28.506 --> 17:30.797
It's hard to
overstate how badly Saddam

17:30.799 --> 17:32.760
was abusing
his people.

17:33.178 --> 17:36.345
Friends of the regime could
get easy access to the medicine.

17:36.347 --> 17:39.265
Others less fortunate
were left to die

17:39.267 --> 17:41.351
from even the
simplest of diseases.

17:47.107 --> 17:48.149
They send bad drugs.

17:49.986 --> 17:51.986
Dump on us their
out-of-date prescriptions.

17:51.988 --> 17:54.113
Thank him for uhh,
bringing this to me

17:54.115 --> 17:56.365
and tell him I will
definitely look into it.

17:59.287 --> 18:04.332
He says there's at black
market with Oil for Food pills.

18:12.342 --> 18:16.302
