22:28.181 --> 22:29.721
of the
program's failings.

22:29.723 --> 22:32.600
If we don't do something, this
reports gonna be a disaster.

22:32.602 --> 22:34.227
Don't you
get the final say?

22:34.229 --> 22:36.645
Sadly, no.

22:36.647 --> 22:41.484
UN protocol requires the
regional director sign off

22:41.486 --> 22:44.821
on the report.

22:44.823 --> 22:46.698
And what's our agenda?

22:46.700 --> 22:48.824
Our agenda?

22:48.826 --> 22:51.119
That little girl.

22:51.121 --> 22:53.496
At the hospital.

22:53.498 --> 22:57.208
God help anyone
who gets in our way.

22:57.210 --> 22:59.459
Yeah.

23:16.061 --> 23:17.604
I had a son once.

23:20.066 --> 23:23.611
Died of
the flu, just a baby.

23:25.654 --> 23:27.031
Can you
believe that?

23:28.657 --> 23:34.663
And my wife, we
couldn't make another.

23:37.625 --> 23:38.625
Sorry.

23:39.626 --> 23:40.961
Thirty years ago.

23:42.630 --> 23:43.965
How did you put it?

23:45.508 --> 23:46.884
I had my cry.

23:51.056 --> 23:51.890
Flu.

23:56.060 --> 23:56.894
You tired?

23:58.270 --> 23:59.105
No.

23:59.564 --> 24:00.645
Youth.

24:00.647 --> 24:01.940
Fuck.

24:15.538 --> 24:18.664
You know, for someone who speaks
for other people for a living,

24:18.666 --> 24:20.084
you don't talk much.

24:22.878 --> 24:26.672
I couldn't help but notice
you were not surprised

24:26.674 --> 24:29.677
when the doctor spoke of
black market medicine.

24:30.929 --> 24:32.303
No I wasn't.

24:34.348 --> 24:35.808
Will you
tell your boss?

24:37.143 --> 24:41.562
Yeah, we already know there's
some corruption in the program.

24:41.564 --> 24:44.315
Outside Baghdad
it's much worse.

24:44.317 --> 24:47.110
Rations diverted,
power cut off.

24:47.112 --> 24:48.779
Extortion, bribes.

24:51.324 --> 24:54.786
I'll uhh, make sure
Pasha knows that too.

25:06.839 --> 25:09.341
You have something
you want to ask me?

25:11.051 --> 25:12.927
Is it
about Madame?

25:12.929 --> 25:15.595
That your boss wants you
to find the secret button

25:15.597 --> 25:18.350
he can push to bend
her to his will?

25:18.727 --> 25:23.729
I can tell you:
it does not exist.

25:23.731 --> 25:25.482
I'm just trying
to do my job.

25:35.367 --> 25:39.873
But your
predecessor Abhek...

25:41.040 --> 25:44.043
His car accident was
not an accident.

25:47.963 --> 25:51.091
That's a pretty big
accusation to make.

26:12.614 --> 26:14.865
Why are you
telling me this?

26:16.284 --> 26:19.037
He was murdered because
of something he uncovered.

26:19.871 --> 26:22.205
Something in
Oil for Food?

26:22.207 --> 26:24.207
I don't know.

26:24.209 --> 26:25.250
Maybe.

26:26.419 --> 26:30.212
He was fearful of
someone inside United Nations.

26:30.214 --> 26:32.424
A facilitator
of corruption.

26:34.760 --> 26:37.221
You need to be
very, very careful.

27:18.262 --> 27:20.138
Good evening.

27:20.140 --> 27:21.389
Please.

27:29.273 --> 27:32.482
The Mukhabarat, you see,
were concerned to inspect

27:32.484 --> 27:34.276
your sleeping chambers
for the existence

27:34.278 --> 27:36.071
of any
surveillance device.

27:36.405 --> 27:40.158
This as a courtesy, for
your security, of course.

27:40.160 --> 27:43.076
Why don't you start by
telling me who you are?

27:43.078 --> 27:45.621
Are you enjoying your visit
to Mesopotamia, Mr. Sullivan?

27:46.750 --> 27:49.083
First one,
if I'm not mistaken yes?

27:49.085 --> 27:52.378
Such a difficult, stressful
time for everyone here.

27:52.380 --> 27:54.796
The Great Satan keeps
threatening to bomb the city

27:54.798 --> 27:58.343
meanwhile, the
sanctions cut deep.

27:58.345 --> 27:59.344
Baghdad puts...

27:59.346 --> 28:01.013
Why don't you
get to the point?

28:03.641 --> 28:05.725
You will find on
the bureau behind me

28:05.727 --> 28:08.353
an envelope containing
a small honorarium.

28:08.355 --> 28:11.146
We greatly admire the work you
are doing for the Iraqi...

28:11.148 --> 28:12.648
It's late.

28:12.650 --> 28:14.844
I'd like you
to leave, please.

28:20.991 --> 28:27.037
No disrespect
was meant by it.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.891
Don't forget your envelope.

28:57.487 --> 29:00.363
Can't blame them for
trying, it's nothing.

29:00.365 --> 29:01.700
You handled it perfectly.

29:05.036 --> 29:08.456
What about what the
interpreter said about Abhek?

29:09.499 --> 29:11.209
I don't believe it.

29:11.792 --> 29:15.587
Maybe she's a spy for
Saddam sent to rattle us.

29:18.258 --> 29:19.507
You look
like shit, kid.

29:19.509 --> 29:22.095
Fuck,
eat something.

29:35.817 --> 29:36.815
I'm sorry.

29:39.528 --> 29:40.652
Excuse me?

29:42.615 --> 29:45.408
I'd been warned,
but I was still shocked

29:45.410 --> 29:48.288
by the criticism from UN staff
against the sanctions.

29:49.038 --> 29:52.289
Pasha was right, every
department had an agenda.

29:52.291 --> 29:54.292
They were working
across purposes.

29:54.294 --> 29:58.755
They played right into
Madame Dupre's hands.

30:07.848 --> 30:09.306
Shut up!

30:10.894 --> 30:13.438
You sound like
Saddam's puppets all of you.

30:14.064 --> 30:16.521
Do I need to point out the
serious fucking consequences

30:16.523 --> 30:18.607
to the Iraqi people,
if we fail to continue...

30:18.609 --> 30:19.441
You violated...

30:20.319 --> 30:24.447
Are you
fucking kidding me!?

30:24.449 --> 30:26.449
It's not our place
to question the decisions

30:26.451 --> 30:30.952
of The Security Council.

30:30.954 --> 30:32.456
We implement them.

30:34.041 --> 30:38.335
Absent of
all politics.

30:38.337 --> 30:41.924
And yes, it's a hard
fucking job sometimes.

30:43.926 --> 30:45.759
But if
you can't do it,

30:45.761 --> 30:48.972
I suggest you turn in your
fucking credentials and go home.

31:00.693 --> 31:01.942
I knew
from my research

31:01.944 --> 31:04.778
that our biggest worry
was Kurdistan.

31:04.780 --> 31:07.699
As long as Saddam was
in power it was gonna take

31:07.701 --> 31:10.075
all of Pasha's considerable
diplomatic skills

31:10.077 --> 31:13.121
to keep the Kurd's from
undermining the report.

31:13.123 --> 31:18.543
The rations, when they come, are
always half what was promised.

31:18.545 --> 31:20.795
The North is a protectorate,
so unfortunately...

31:20.797 --> 31:23.171
They had been hurt
harder under the sanctions

31:23.173 --> 31:26.008
than any other region
and while Oil for Food

31:26.010 --> 31:28.510
was providing
some relief,

31:28.512 --> 31:30.971
it had helped sustain the very
regime that oppressed them.

31:30.973 --> 31:34.142
The Kurds have plenty
of money to buy their own food,

31:34.144 --> 31:35.809
from that
black market oil.

31:35.811 --> 31:37.144
Minister, if you
would allow me...

31:37.146 --> 31:39.188
The Kurdish
conflict with Iraq goes back

31:39.190 --> 31:41.026
nearly a century.

31:41.734 --> 31:44.651
Saddam Hussein took
it to a whole new level.

31:44.653 --> 31:47.988
Forced displacement,
mass detention and torture.

31:47.990 --> 31:51.074
And then, when that didn't work,
he resorted to landmines

31:51.076 --> 31:53.119
and cluster bombs,
sarin gas

31:53.121 --> 31:55.037
and nerve agents Killing
tens of thousands

31:55.039 --> 31:58.165
and crippling tens of
thousands more.

31:58.167 --> 32:00.125
A reign of
terror that included

32:00.127 --> 32:02.879
the worst single act of chemical
genocide ever committed

32:02.881 --> 32:04.963
against a
civilian population.

32:04.965 --> 32:08.676
Kurds are dying for
simply being Kurdish.

32:08.678 --> 32:10.553
And in a shuttle
diplomacy between

32:10.555 --> 32:14.140
two sworn enemies,
I watched Pasha work his magic.

32:14.142 --> 32:17.267
...About how the
most beloved food to Allah,

32:17.269 --> 32:20.438
is that which is touched
by many hands.

32:20.440 --> 32:21.271
Fuck!

32:21.273 --> 32:22.315
This is all I need.

32:22.317 --> 32:23.607
The Kurdish Minister's
right though,

32:23.609 --> 32:24.901
from what
I've been told,

32:24.903 --> 32:25.901
they're getting
completely screwed.

32:25.903 --> 32:27.569
I know he's right.

32:27.571 --> 32:30.698
It's in the fucking field reports,
but we have to keep a lid on it.

32:30.700 --> 32:33.241
The choice can't be to
feed everyone or feed no one.

32:33.243 --> 32:37.162
It has to be to feed
as many as possible.

32:41.211 --> 32:44.003
I have to go back to
New York tomorrow.

32:44.005 --> 32:46.171
I need you
to stay focused.

32:46.173 --> 32:47.008
Of course.

32:48.926 --> 32:50.176
Here's your
travel itinerary.

32:50.178 --> 32:53.723
You are connected to
Kuwait, you land in JFK at 5 PM.

32:55.724 --> 32:59.267
Dupre is going to freeze
you out for the final report.

32:59.269 --> 33:01.230
Her opus
indictment of Oil for Food.

33:03.942 --> 33:08.151
Okay, then why am
I staying here then?

33:08.153 --> 33:10.196
In a few days, you'll
receive some photographs.

33:10.198 --> 33:12.030
You'll want
Hassan to see them

33:12.032 --> 33:14.074
because you won't understand
what they could mean.

33:14.076 --> 33:17.161
Your task is to make sure
he shows them to Dupre

33:17.163 --> 33:18.832
by insisting
he shouldn't.

33:21.250 --> 33:22.709
You're asking
me if I'll...

33:22.711 --> 33:23.918
A trap, yes.

33:23.920 --> 33:26.254
She'll fall into it,
and we'll be rid of her.

33:30.218 --> 33:33.219
Kid,
it's diplomacy,

33:33.221 --> 33:36.180
which sometimes requires
removing obstacles

33:36.182 --> 33:38.018
that stand in the way of
successful outcome.

33:42.230 --> 33:44.274
Can I trust you
again with this one?

33:46.859 --> 33:49.861
I mean, how big of a lie
am I gonna be telling?

33:49.863 --> 33:50.864
Not lie.

33:52.865 --> 33:55.451
Just the opportunity to
draw a wrong conclusion.

34:16.347 --> 34:17.353
Morning.

34:36.117 --> 34:39.911
Just so you know, Madame says
you won't be reading the report

34:39.913 --> 34:43.206
until it's finished
and she sign off on it.

34:43.208 --> 34:45.166
Well, Pasha said he
wants me to help.

34:45.168 --> 34:47.501
People in hell
want ice water.

34:47.503 --> 34:51.338
We're just ponds in a
bigger game, you and me.

34:51.340 --> 34:52.509
Sorry, Michael.

34:54.135 --> 34:54.969
Hassan.

34:56.346 --> 35:00.016
At least you can help me arrange
an interpreter for a field trip.

35:02.226 --> 35:05.228
I wanna open one of these boxes
and check the expiration dates.

35:07.065 --> 35:08.523
He says he's the
company representative.

35:08.525 --> 35:11.066
Tell him I wanna open
one of these boxes.

35:24.541 --> 35:26.459
These pills
expired in 1999.

35:29.378 --> 35:32.546
Sick people will get
sicker or die because of these.

35:35.217 --> 35:37.175
Every box
needs to be checked,

35:37.177 --> 35:39.220
the out of date
medicine needs to be destroyed

35:39.222 --> 35:41.264
and the manufacture
will have to replace it

35:41.266 --> 35:42.599
at their own expense.

35:51.275 --> 35:55.237
I should warn you, everyone
here thinks I'm your prostitute.

35:57.114 --> 35:59.158
Well, I guess we should
split the check then.

36:00.409 --> 36:02.409
You can't really
just have a date

36:02.411 --> 36:04.579
with an un-chaperoned
woman in Iraq.

36:04.581 --> 36:06.789
There are rituals
and traditions.

36:06.791 --> 36:09.085
Do you wanna
call it off then?

36:11.588 --> 36:14.423
Did you tell your boss
what I said about Ahbek?

36:17.217 --> 36:18.677
Yeah I did, he uhh...

36:19.471 --> 36:22.097
He thinks you might
be a government spy.

36:33.860 --> 36:35.278
So are you?
A spy?

36:37.237 --> 36:38.614
Is that
a serious question?

36:39.449 --> 36:42.159
Well, that's a
pretty evasive answer.

36:43.869 --> 36:51.333
No.

36:51.335 --> 36:53.671
Now it's
my turn to ask you.

36:54.422 --> 36:55.340
Okay.

36:57.257 --> 36:59.508
What are you
doing here?

36:59.510 --> 37:02.387
Well umm, I'm doing
a status report

37:02.389 --> 37:04.722
for the Oil for Food program
and then I'm gonna...

37:05.684 --> 37:09.309
I mean today, with
the spoiled medicine.

37:09.311 --> 37:13.481
What you did had nothing to
do with writing your report.

37:13.483 --> 37:14.776
You took action.

37:15.527 --> 37:18.487
It was risky
and rather brave.

37:19.739 --> 37:21.699
Was that just
to impress me?

37:24.744 --> 37:27.288
I'm not here to
just be a functionary.

37:28.664 --> 37:32.793
I took this job for a reason
because I wanna help people

37:34.545 --> 37:38.338
and I wanna
make a difference.

37:38.340 --> 37:40.883
Make a difference?

37:40.885 --> 37:42.220
Exactly.

37:45.306 --> 37:46.266
I'll drink to that.

37:47.391 --> 37:48.393
Cheers.

37:52.438 --> 37:53.771
They're not
gonna bomb Baghdad,

37:53.773 --> 37:55.731
not without getting
The UN staffers out first.

37:55.733 --> 37:56.566
Mr. Sullivan?

37:56.568 --> 37:57.483
Yeah?

37:57.485 --> 37:58.525
This has
come for you.

37:58.527 --> 38:00.028
Thanks.

38:00.030 --> 38:01.362
Lil, I gotta go.

38:01.364 --> 38:02.487
Who sent this?

38:02.489 --> 38:04.490
It was left on the
night desk, sir.

38:20.592 --> 38:22.133
Are those
Oil for Food trucks?

38:22.135 --> 38:25.010
Yeah, but I don't know
the source of them.

38:25.012 --> 38:28.597
If they're real, they're
proof that we're being gamed

38:28.599 --> 38:30.057
by Saddam's regime.

38:30.059 --> 38:32.559
Yeah, If, I still don't
think we should trust them.

38:32.561 --> 38:36.023
Using our trucks to deliver
weapons, I mean, what the fuck?

38:36.940 --> 38:39.525
I'm just gonna pack them up
into a courier pouch,

38:39.527 --> 38:41.443
see what Pasha says.

38:41.445 --> 38:42.739
No, no, no.

38:44.574 --> 38:45.865
Let me show
Christina first.

38:45.867 --> 38:48.492
No, no, no chance.

38:48.494 --> 38:50.746
It's okay,
what do you call it?

38:51.414 --> 38:52.582
"Chain of command."

38:55.501 --> 38:56.335
Okay.

39:23.862 --> 39:24.987
Hi.

39:24.989 --> 39:27.699
Hey.

39:27.701 --> 39:30.200
I need to show
you something.

39:30.202 --> 39:31.621
Okay.

39:38.043 --> 39:41.713
They are friends.

39:41.715 --> 39:42.716
Okay.

40:21.378 --> 40:26.175
So, this place
isn't here, officially.

40:27.052 --> 40:29.927
These are the graves
of Kurdish civilians that

40:29.929 --> 40:33.432
Saddam Hussein one day decided
no longer needed to live.

40:34.726 --> 40:38.144
Gas,
Sarin, Tabun, VX.

40:38.146 --> 40:40.065
The smell
of sweet apples.

40:42.400 --> 40:46.735
He doesn't care about your
sanctions or resolutions.

40:46.737 --> 40:50.449
He's the Angel of
Death... Azrael.

40:52.869 --> 40:53.870
You're Kurdish.

40:55.288 --> 40:58.541
My parents were
intellectuals, active in PUK.

41:00.710 --> 41:02.378
Killed in Halabdja.

41:04.088 --> 41:04.963
I'm sorry.

41:06.382 --> 41:09.758
Nobody in Baghdad knows
I'm Kurdish, Michael.

41:09.760 --> 41:11.344
If Saddam's
police find out.

41:11.346 --> 41:14.097
They will
disappear me.

41:14.099 --> 41:17.432
My friends, they helped Ahbek
uncover a criminal conspiracy

41:17.434 --> 41:21.313
Saddam is using to skim billions
of dollars from Oil for Food.

41:23.023 --> 41:25.900
Ahbek claimed there is a
whole system of corruption that

41:25.902 --> 41:28.735
reaches to the highest levels of
the same Western government

41:28.737 --> 41:30.489
that supports sanctions.

41:31.615 --> 41:33.574
Okay, how did
Ahbek know this?

41:33.576 --> 41:35.827
There is
a rumor of a list.

41:35.829 --> 41:38.912
A list that contains names
of people and organizations

41:38.914 --> 41:42.041
all over the world who are all
getting paid off by Saddam

41:42.043 --> 41:44.253
to keep
this system running.

41:44.713 --> 41:46.713
And Ahbek
had seen it.

41:46.715 --> 41:47.713
Did you bring it?

41:47.715 --> 41:48.715
Yes.

41:48.717 --> 41:50.383
May have
had it on his computer.

41:50.385 --> 41:51.925
You sure
nobody saw you?

41:51.927 --> 41:55.345
The office was empty,
everyone had gone home.

41:55.347 --> 41:56.972
Ahbek, what's
going on with you?

41:56.974 --> 42:00.642
I'm going North
across the border.

42:00.644 --> 42:02.188
It's not safe
for me here.

42:18.746 --> 42:20.164
He made a back up.

42:22.833 --> 42:24.168
But it's encrypted.

42:26.003 --> 42:28.422
We don't have the
resources to decipher it.

42:32.010 --> 42:35.094
Why didn't you take it to
someone more senior in The UN?

42:35.096 --> 42:36.179
I mean, anyone.

42:36.181 --> 42:37.220
Madame Dupre?

42:37.222 --> 42:39.974
Nobody would
listen to her.

42:39.976 --> 42:43.394
It's important who
delivers the list.

42:43.396 --> 42:45.854
No one can accuse you
of being Partisan

42:45.856 --> 42:48.231
or of having any
agenda but the truth.

42:48.233 --> 42:50.319
I'm not gonna
front this, Nashim.

42:51.237 --> 42:53.320
I'm not
gonna do that.

42:53.322 --> 42:54.613
No, I don't
want that.

42:54.615 --> 42:57.909
I just want you to take it back
with you and find someone

42:57.911 --> 42:59.704
who can break
the encryption.

43:00.204 --> 43:03.875
Then, together we
can decide what to do.

43:32.027 --> 43:32.901
Shit!

43:32.903 --> 43:33.905
It's the Mukhabarat.

43:37.242 --> 43:40.327
Are you fucking
kidding me, Jesus!

43:54.759 --> 43:57.885
There must be
a mistake, I'm a UN official.

43:57.887 --> 43:58.930
The young diplomat.

44:00.389 --> 44:03.141
You know it's very
dangerous for you to be in this

44:03.143 --> 44:05.394
god forsaken
desert unescorted.

44:05.978 --> 44:08.396
The Mukhabarat were concerned
that you might have been

44:08.398 --> 44:10.858
kidnapped by
nefarious individuals.

44:12.735 --> 44:14.945
Consider this a courtesy.

44:15.362 --> 44:16.498
Your Papers.

44:27.708 --> 44:30.083
I tell you this, with all
humility, Mr. Sullivan

44:30.085 --> 44:31.918
because I'm
sure it won't happen again.

44:31.920 --> 44:33.503
Your recent visit to

44:33.505 --> 44:35.965
the pharmaceutical
distribution service

44:35.967 --> 44:40.094
that was unnecessarily
provocative, yes?

44:40.096 --> 44:42.597
It would be in everyone's
best interest, in the future,

44:42.599 --> 44:48.561
were to decide such inspections
were no longer necessary.

44:51.148 --> 44:53.317
She is my interpreter
alright! I told you!

45:06.539 --> 45:08.956
Go! Now.

45:08.958 --> 45:10.749
Before they
change their minds.

45:10.751 --> 45:12.668
Get in the car.

45:28.353 --> 45:29.476
He kept my papers.

45:31.690 --> 45:35.360
It's only a question of time now
before they find out who I am.

46:05.681 --> 46:07.182
Nashim Huesseni.

46:14.398 --> 46:16.398
- Where is the girl?
- What girl?

46:16.400 --> 46:17.983
The Kurdish girl?

46:17.985 --> 46:19.068
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- You're lying!

46:19.070 --> 46:20.528
- I-I don't know what you're talking about!
- Don't lie!

46:20.530 --> 46:21.862
I don't know
where she is.

46:21.864 --> 46:23.197
We saw you
with her!

46:23.199 --> 46:24.907
Yeah, I know, but I don't
know where she is, okay.

46:24.909 --> 46:28.702
Let me just...
Let me just make a call.

46:28.704 --> 46:30.331
I don't know
where she is.

46:31.248 --> 46:32.623
Get out!

46:32.625 --> 46:34.541
You have no
jurisdiction here!

46:34.543 --> 46:35.502
Out!

46:46.056 --> 46:50.307
It's Michael Sullivan with
The Baghdad Oil for Food office.

46:50.309 --> 46:51.143
Yeah.

46:52.478 --> 46:53.312
Yeah.

46:54.773 --> 46:57.525
I need to arrange a UNLP
for one of our staffers.

46:58.693 --> 46:59.527
Mhm.

47:00.903 --> 47:04.907
And the name is
Nashim Huesseni.

47:18.672 --> 47:19.753
Hey.

47:19.755 --> 47:21.338
I took all
I could carry.

47:21.340 --> 47:23.090
This will get you
into the U.S.

47:23.092 --> 47:25.885
The High Commission for Refugees
will help you get a visa.

47:25.887 --> 47:26.927
I don't know.

47:26.929 --> 47:28.679
I can go to
Kurdish part of Turkey.

47:28.681 --> 47:29.972
I have some
friends there.

47:29.974 --> 47:31.724
No, you'll be
safer in New York.

47:31.726 --> 47:32.974
We'll get you to
The U.S.

47:32.976 --> 47:36.144
then we de-encrypt
the list together.

47:38.023 --> 47:40.691
Go, you cannot
be seen with me.

47:40.693 --> 47:44.945
Whatever happens...

47:44.947 --> 47:46.949
Just promise me
you'll let me know.

47:48.952 --> 47:53.121
Whatever happens,
happens.

47:53.123 --> 47:54.374
Right?

48:00.963 --> 48:01.922
Thank you.

48:04.050 --> 48:05.010
Thank you.

48:24.153 --> 48:26.112
Would you please
come to my office?

48:26.114 --> 48:27.740
Immediately.

48:31.744 --> 48:34.037
Did you really expect me
to fall for these...

48:34.039 --> 48:36.039
These, I don't even know
what to call them.

48:36.041 --> 48:38.166
Garbage.

48:38.168 --> 48:39.958
What was the plan?

48:39.960 --> 48:41.793
Trick me into
releasing them?

48:41.795 --> 48:44.796
And then force me out when the
evidence comes that it's false?

48:44.798 --> 48:47.592
I'm at a loss to even know
what you're talking about.

48:47.594 --> 48:49.885
Madame, I was sent some
documents and Hassam

48:49.887 --> 48:51.970
wanted to show them
to you, that's it.

48:51.972 --> 48:54.974
You are finished in
the UN, do you hear me?

48:54.976 --> 48:56.099
Your career is over!

48:56.101 --> 48:57.851
What would you
have him do?

48:57.853 --> 48:59.186
He got
some photos...

48:59.188 --> 49:00.188
Shame on you.

49:00.190 --> 49:01.900
Shame on
both of you!

49:04.027 --> 49:05.776
The report
is finished.

49:05.778 --> 49:09.030
It tells the truth about
the failure of Oil For Food.

49:09.032 --> 49:12.909
The files are digital,
watermarked, time, date

49:12.911 --> 49:16.704
and I have secure copies so
you can't change anything

49:16.706 --> 49:18.164
when it goes
to New York.

49:18.166 --> 49:21.041
The battle is over,
Costa, and you have lost.

49:21.043 --> 49:22.876
The Security Council
will make their decision

49:22.878 --> 49:24.670
based on the facts.

49:34.181 --> 49:38.016
She's not budging.

49:38.018 --> 49:40.144
Well, fuck.

49:40.146 --> 49:42.646
Nothing more for
you to do there, kid.

49:42.648 --> 49:45.023
Take the next UN
flight and come home.

49:47.070 --> 49:48.276
Don't worry about it.

50:09.925 --> 50:13.927
Excuse me sir,
can I see your passport?

50:13.929 --> 50:15.139
Uh, yeah sure.

50:24.190 --> 50:25.273
Mr. Sullivan?

50:25.275 --> 50:27.027
I'm gonna need you
to come with us.

50:48.213 --> 50:49.382
Michael,
how're you doing?

50:51.925 --> 50:53.342
I have
nothing for you.

50:53.344 --> 50:56.262
No, that's okay,
I got something for you.

50:56.264 --> 50:59.768
Christina Dupre is dead.

51:01.311 --> 51:04.064
They found her a few
hours ago alone at home.

51:04.521 --> 51:05.898
Heart attack.

51:06.358 --> 51:14.155
At least that's
what they're saying.

51:14.157 --> 51:16.284
Wait, w-what do you mean,
"That's what they're saying?"

51:19.496 --> 51:21.329
What do you think
happened, Mike?

51:27.003 --> 51:29.753
